            <title>[CASSANDRA-13410] nodetool upgradesstables/scrub/compact ignores system tables</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-13410</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-11627&quot; title=&quot;Streaming and other ops should filter out all LocalStrategy keyspaces, not just system keyspaces&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-11627&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-11627&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; changed the behavior of nodetool commands that work across all keyspaces. Sometimes it&apos;s OK (not compacting system.peers when you call compact probably isn&apos;t going to anger anyone), but sometimes it&apos;s not (disableautocompaction, flush, upgradesstables, etc).&lt;/p&gt;
