                            <comment id="15956868" author="pauloricardomg" created="Wed, 5 Apr 2017 13:37:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the record this also affects 2.2 and was actually introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5483&quot; title=&quot;Repair tracing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-5483&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-5483&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, as reported by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-11830&quot; title=&quot;&amp;quot;nodetool flush&amp;quot; not flushing system keyspace&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-11830&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-11830&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, so I&apos;m closing that as duplicate of this. But given 2.2 is nearly in critical-fixes-only mode, and would require a different patch I think it&apos;s fine to keep this 3.0+ only.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
